Q> What is Connection Pooling?

first understand why this concept will came:-

if we write code for geting connecction to db internally many thing happen like:-
1> Network connection is created
2> Authentication happens
3> Session is created inside DB
4> Memory allocated
5> Server process created

This is very costly operation (take time + resources).

Now imagine:
  .> 1000 users hitting your website
  .> Each request creates new connection
  .> Each request closes connecton
 
Then what happens:-  
  Database will become slow 
  and too many ssessions occurs
  System crash chance is high
  
  thats why conection pooling concept are came.
  
  Connection pooling:-
        Connection Pooling is a technique where a group (pool) of database 
        connections are created in advance and reused instead of creating
        new connections every time.
  
 
 
 
  
  